hi... sorry for not the late reply, the Op type not registered '*' in binary is a know issue in java land, since by default tf.contrib project .so didn't get package within the java distribution can be addessed by TensorFlow.loadLibrary() #10454 (comment)

Meanwhile, for the tensorflow in python having this kind of error could be soemthing to do with misconfiguration with bazel? i'll have to spend more time into reproduce the error to achieve a conclusion

body:
hi... sorry for not the late reply, the ` Op type not registered '*' in binary` is a know issue in java land, since by default  tf.contrib project `.so` didn't get package within the java distribution can be addessed by `TensorFlow.loadLibrary()` https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/10454#issuecomment-344139462

Meanwhile, for the tensorflow in python having this kind of error could be soemthing to do with misconfiguration with bazel? i'll have to spend more time into reproduce the error to achieve a conclusion
